														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2652286">
									

<p>I'm a fan of the concept, and much prefer it to many of the contest entries - there's a kernel of nastiness which feels so right.</p>
<p>That said, I realised quite quickly where this was going (when each of the first three speeches refers to a particular type of action, Chekov's gun starts to apply). As such, I found the last few lines very clunky and obvious, which undermined the dry tone.</p>
<p>I was all set to downvote, when I finally got hit by the pun in the title. That was sufficiently subtle for my tastes, and worth upvoting.</p>

