<p>Yeah, the ending was initially a lot more subtle, relying wholly on the Chekov's gun to drive the point home, and ending with the sentence &quot;Well, at least the food's still decent&quot;. I preferred that version TBH, but was told it was <em>too</em> subtle, so I changed it. It was hard striking the right balance, but this is the version that received the best reaction in the forums. Your comment is making me consider changing the ending again, though&#8230; maybe just ending with &quot;at least meat's back on the menu&quot;?</p>
<p>Glad you still liked parts of it, in any case - including the title. :)</p>
<p>EDIT: Fuck it, I changed it. YOLO. Hopefully this is better now. The word &quot;meat&quot; in the last line should be enough for people to get what's going on, I think.</p>

							</div>

								
